<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,978,1938]" box="[151,693,978,1003]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,979,1003]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
Male 8.20–8.80 mm., female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,978,1938]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,463,1015,1039]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">External Morphology.</emphasis>
Large, robust species. General color of dorsum yellow and black; forewings concolorous brown throughout; mesonotum black; pronotum black with small yellow spots; crown yellow; eyes translucent (Plate IIIB); face predominately yellow; clypeus with row of short black transverse bands on each side, suffused with longitudinal black stripe medially, 3 small spots in center of lora, black spot under each eye.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,978,1938]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Head broad, distinctly narrower than pronotum, anterior margin broadly rounded; crown broad, wider than eye, produced anteriorly about ¼ of entire length, foveate on each side of middle; eyes large, elongate ovoid, pronotum slightly longer than crown, surface bullated; mesonotum large, about twice as long as pronotum; clypeus long, broad, lateral margin broadly convex, median longitudinal carina prominent; clypellus about 1/3 as long as clypeus, narrow, median longitudinal ridge inflated in basal 2/3, lateral margins flared apically.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,978,1938]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,378,1338,1363]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view large, triangulate, caudodorsal process moderately long, robust, caudoventral process short, broad basally, apex ligulate, closely appressed to base of caudodorsal process (
<figureCitation box="[1329,1423,1374,1398]" captionStart="FIGURES 143–150" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[236,1358,190,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-71@44.[203,1380,177,1908]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 143–150. Docalidia gigantea, sp. nov. (143) pygofer, lateral view; (144) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (145) right style, lateral view; (146) right style, dorsal view; (147) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (148) aedeagus, ventral view; (149) connective, caudal view; (150) dorsal connective, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5281743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5281743/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig 143</figureCitation>
); right subgenital plate long, very narrow throughout length, twisted medially, setaceous along middle of outer lateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[245,343,1446,1470]" captionStart="FIGURES 143–150" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[236,1358,190,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-71@44.[203,1380,177,1908]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 143–150. Docalidia gigantea, sp. nov. (143) pygofer, lateral view; (144) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (145) right style, lateral view; (146) right style, dorsal view; (147) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (148) aedeagus, ventral view; (149) connective, caudal view; (150) dorsal connective, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5281743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5281743/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 144</figureCitation>
); right style extremely long, nearly twice as long as aedeagus, very narrow, broadly curved in lateral view, row of short setae in distal 2/3 on inner lateral margin in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1077,1245,1482,1506]" captionStart="FIGURES 143–150" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[236,1358,190,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-71@44.[203,1380,177,1908]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 143–150. Docalidia gigantea, sp. nov. (143) pygofer, lateral view; (144) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (145) right style, lateral view; (146) right style, dorsal view; (147) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (148) aedeagus, ventral view; (149) connective, caudal view; (150) dorsal connective, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5281743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5281743/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Figs. 145, 146</figureCitation>
); aedeagus long, narrow, shaft broad in basal half, narrowed in distal half in lateral view, flanged near middle and subapically, in ventral view shaft with dorsal apodeme flared laterally, gonopore submedial, exiting ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[1252,1423,1554,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 143–150" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[236,1358,190,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-71@44.[203,1380,177,1908]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 143–150. Docalidia gigantea, sp. nov. (143) pygofer, lateral view; (144) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (145) right style, lateral view; (146) right style, dorsal view; (147) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (148) aedeagus, ventral view; (149) connective, caudal view; (150) dorsal connective, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5281743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5281743/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Figs. 147, 148</figureCitation>
); connective T-shaped, arms broad, membrane absent, stem long, broad (
<figureCitation box="[948,1047,1590,1614]" captionStart="FIGURES 143–150" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[236,1358,190,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-71@44.[203,1380,177,1908]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 143–150. Docalidia gigantea, sp. nov. (143) pygofer, lateral view; (144) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (145) right style, lateral view; (146) right style, dorsal view; (147) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (148) aedeagus, ventral view; (149) connective, caudal view; (150) dorsal connective, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5281743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5281743/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 149</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective short, strapped shape, broadly basally, tapered distally in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[766,864,1626,1650]" captionStart="FIGURES 143–150" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[236,1358,190,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-71@44.[203,1380,177,1908]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 143–150. Docalidia gigantea, sp. nov. (143) pygofer, lateral view; (144) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (145) right style, lateral view; (146) right style, dorsal view; (147) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (148) aedeagus, ventral view; (149) connective, caudal view; (150) dorsal connective, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5281743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5281743/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 150</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
